column5: Hi all,  Good fall bite this afternoon, all 30' to 45' FOW on jig and slip bobber with 4" to 6" minnows.   Also got a few birds on the way in.   Rained almost all day, but was around 10C with little to no wind....i'll take that for a day in late October !     <iframe width="420" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/V0de72Ierb0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
if having two left feet means you cant dance then you must be able to bustamoove pretty good Nice shooting !
nice cooler shot. Looks like a great day on the water
And he has the hoof on the wrong foot!      Friday's supper is looking good!      Gangnam Style!    Was an awesome day.....i really appreciated being out there yesterday....countin' my blessings!

That's just bloody awesome Simon    You guys sure got into some brutes in this outing   You got to love it when the big ones come out to play and a couple of birds to boot Great job you two and thanks for sharing! Jacques
Sweet, how was dinner  Some real nice fish there Simon
You guys use BIG bobbers   Nice fish and birdies Simon.
Simon, Was the moose leg left along the road from a harvest?Nice fishing and shooting.
Man you guys got some nice eyes!....  Thanks for sharing!
Another excellent report, Simon. A fine supper of fish, fowl and gigot as well.
Great report Simon!! Keep them coming!!
Always a pleasure to browse through your reports. Another successful outing!
